}{}$ \frac{1}{4} $\end{document}14-volume of 10 M LiCl was added, mixed, and incubated at 4 °C for 6 h. After precipitation for 6 h, the sample was centrifuged for 10 min at 12,000 rpm at 4 °C, and the supernatant was discarded. The sediment was washed twice with 500 µL 75% EtOH and 500 µL anhydrous alcohol precooled at –20 °C, respectively. The sample was dried for 5 min, then resuspended in 50 µL DEPC-treated water. Total RNA concentration and integrity were determined, and high-quality RNAs were used for cDNA library construction.
